This is not an Eclipse bug. 
The problem is that you are trying to write to a URL Connection to a File URL, not an HTTP URL because 
getDocumentBase() is returning file://xxx. Eclipse uses appletViewer to run applets by default, the URL 
your getting is probably coming from that executable. This would explain why you get different 
behavior when running in a web browser. I don't know how Netbeans handles applets (I prefer Eclipse 
:-)

The following code produces the same error.

import java.io.OutputStream;
import java.net.URL;
import java.net.URLConnection;

public class FileURLWriter {
	public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
		URL url = new URL("file:///Users/kevinbarnes/Junk/	foo.txt");
		URLConnection conn = url.openConnection();
		OutputStream out = conn.getOutputStream();
		out.write(new byte[]{1});
	}
}
